Hannon Armstrong Sustainable
Infrastructure Capital Inc., a renewable-energy financing
company, plans to raise as much as $100 million in an initial
public offering to purchase assets.  The company, based in Annapolis, Maryland, plans to
organize as a real estate investment trust, according to a
filing today. The amount sought is a placeholder used to
calculate registration fees and may change.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Wade at 
